// Unit 4: Add & Subtract to 1,000
_mergeUnitData(3, {"lessons":[{"points":["Same rules as 2-digit, just one more column!","Add ones → tens → hundreds","Regroup (regroup) whenever a column reaches 10 or more"],"examples":[{"c":"#d35400","tag":"Regrouping in Ones AND Tens","p":"347 + 286 = ?","s":"<table class=\"col-math\"><tr class=\"cm-regroup\"><td></td><td>1</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td></td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>7</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-bottom\"><td class=\"cm-op\">+</td><td>2</td><td>8</td><td>6</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-line\"><td colspan=\"4\"><hr></td></tr><tr class=\"cm-result\"><td></td><td>6</td><td>3</td><td>3</td></tr></table><br>Ones: 7+6=13 → write <b>3</b>, regroup <b>1</b> ten<br>Tens: 4+8+1=13 → write <b>3</b>, regroup <b>1</b> ten<br>Hundreds: 3+2+1 = <b>6</b><br><br><button onclick=\"play3dRegroup(this,[3,4,7],[2,8,6])\" class=\"cca-btn\" style=\"background:#d35400\">🎬 Watch Step by Step</button>","a":"347 + 286 = 633 ✅"},{"c":"#d35400","tag":"Regrouping in Ones AND Tens","p":"456 + 378 = ?","s":"<table class=\"col-math\"><tr class=\"cm-regroup\"><td></td><td>1</td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td></td><td>4</td><td>5</td><td>6</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-bottom\"><td class=\"cm-op\">+</td><td>3</td><td>7</td><td>8</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-line\"><td colspan=\"4\"><hr></td></tr><tr class=\"cm-result\"><td></td><td>8</td><td>3</td><td>4</td></tr></table><br>Ones: 6+8=14 → write <b>4</b>, regroup <b>1</b> ten<br>Tens: 5+7+1=13 → write <b>3</b>, regroup <b>1</b> ten<br>Hundreds: 4+3+1 = <b>8</b><br><br><button onclick=\"play3dRegroup(this,[4,5,6],[3,7,8])\" class=\"cca-btn\" style=\"background:#d35400\">🎬 Watch Step by Step</button>","a":"456 + 378 = 834 ✅"},{"c":"#d35400","tag":"Regrouping in Ones Only","p":"523 + 349 = ?","s":"<table class=\"col-math\"><tr class=\"cm-regroup\"><td></td><td></td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td></td><td>5</td><td>2</td><td>3</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-bottom\"><td class=\"cm-op\">+</td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>9</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-line\"><td colspan=\"4\"><hr></td></tr><tr class=\"cm-result\"><td></td><td>8</td><td>7</td><td>2</td></tr></table><br>Ones: 3+9=12 → write <b>2</b>, regroup <b>1</b> ten<br>Tens: 2+4+1=7 (no regroup)<br>Hundreds: 5+3 = <b>8</b><br><br><button onclick=\"play3dRegroup(this,[5,2,3],[3,4,9])\" class=\"cca-btn\" style=\"background:#d35400\">🎬 Watch Step by Step</button>","a":"523 + 349 = 872 ✅"},{"c":"#d35400","tag":"Regrouping in Ones Only","p":"615 + 247 = ?","s":"<table class=\"col-math\"><tr class=\"cm-regroup\"><td></td><td></td><td>1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td></td><td>6</td><td>1</td><td>5</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-bottom\"><td class=\"cm-op\">+</td><td>2</td><td>4</td><td>7</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-line\"><td colspan=\"4\"><hr></td></tr><tr class=\"cm-result\"><td></td><td>8</td><td>6</td><td>2</td></tr></table><br>Ones: 5+7=12 → write <b>2</b>, regroup <b>1</b> ten<br>Tens: 1+4+1=6 (no regroup)<br>Hundreds: 6+2 = <b>8</b><br><br><button onclick=\"play3dRegroup(this,[6,1,5],[2,4,7])\" class=\"cca-btn\" style=\"background:#d35400\">🎬 Watch Step by Step</button>","a":"615 + 247 = 862 ✅"}],"practice":[{"q":"234 + 152 = ?","a":"386","h":"Ones: 4+2=6. Tens: 3+5=8. Hundreds: 2+1=3","e":"➕"},{"q":"345 + 278 = ?","a":"623","h":"Ones: 5+8=13 regroup 1 ten. Tens: 4+7+1=12 regroup 1 ten. Hundreds: 3+2+1=6","e":"🍎"},{"q":"456 + 367 = ?","a":"823","h":"Ones: 6+7=13 regroup 1 ten. Tens: 5+6+1=12 regroup 1 ten. Hundreds: 4+3+1=8","e":"🍊"}],"qBank":[{"t":"What is 347 + 286?","o":["572","681","633","714"],"a":2,"e":"Add the ones first: 7 + 6 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 4 + 8 + 1 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 3 + 2 + 1 = 6.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 456 + 378?","o":["834","762","871","913"],"a":0,"e":"Add the ones first: 6 + 8 = 14, write 4 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 5 + 7 + 1 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 4 + 3 + 1 = 8.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 523 + 349?","o":["872","801","913","754"],"a":0,"e":"Add the ones first: 3 + 9 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 2 + 4 + 1 = 7. Then hundreds: 5 + 3 = 8.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 267 + 435?","o":["702","651","743","815"],"a":0,"e":"Add the ones first: 7 + 5 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 6 + 3 + 1 = 10, write 0 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 2 + 4 + 1 = 7.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 548 + 276?","o":["763","871","912","824"],"a":3,"e":"Add the ones first: 8 + 6 = 14, write 4 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 4 + 7 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 5 + 2 + 1 = 8.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 381 + 249?","o":["630","573","681","742"],"a":0,"e":"Add the ones first: 1 + 9 = 10, write 0 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 8 + 4 + 1 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 3 + 2 + 1 = 6.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 475 + 356?","o":["763","872","831","914"],"a":2,"e":"Add the ones first: 5 + 6 = 11, write 1 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 7 + 5 + 1 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 4 + 3 + 1 = 8.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 629 + 183?","o":["751","873","812","934"],"a":2,"e":"Add the ones first: 9 + 3 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 2 + 8 + 1 = 11, write 1 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 6 + 1 + 1 = 8.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 157 + 468?","o":["571","673","625","814"],"a":2,"e":"Add the ones first: 7 + 8 = 15, write 5 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 5 + 6 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 1 + 4 + 1 = 6.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 234 + 589?","o":["761","823","874","912"],"a":1,"e":"Add the ones first: 4 + 9 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 3 + 8 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 2 + 5 + 1 = 8.","d":"m"},{"t":"When your ones column adds up to 14, what do you write and regroup?","o":["4, regroup 1 ten","1, regroup 4","14, regroup 0","0, regroup 1 ten4"],"a":0,"e":"Write the 4 in the ones column, then regroup 1 ten over to the tens column.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 648 + 175?","o":["823","764","871","912"],"a":0,"e":"Add the ones first: 8 + 5 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 4 + 7 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 6 + 1 + 1 = 8.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 362 + 479?","o":["763","892","841","914"],"a":2,"e":"Add the ones first: 2 + 9 = 11, write 1 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 6 + 7 + 1 = 14, write 4 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 3 + 4 + 1 = 8.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 793 + 148?","o":["873","982","941","1014"],"a":2,"e":"Add the ones first: 3 + 8 = 11, write 1 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 9 + 4 + 1 = 14, write 4 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 7 + 1 + 1 = 9.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 456 + 289?","o":["671","793","745","814"],"a":2,"e":"Add the ones first: 6 + 9 = 15, write 5 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 5 + 8 + 1 = 14, write 4 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 4 + 2 + 1 = 7.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which addition problem requires regrouping twice?","o":["123+456","301+408","247+368","211+353"],"a":2,"e":"In 247 + 368, the ones give 7 + 8 = 15 (regroup!), and the tens give 4 + 6 + 1 = 11 (regroup again!). That is two regroupings!","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 174 + 368?","o":["542","471","583","624"],"a":0,"e":"Add the ones first: 4 + 8 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 7 + 6 + 1 = 14, write 4 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 1 + 3 + 1 = 5.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 539 + 283?","o":["751","873","934","822"],"a":3,"e":"Add the ones first: 9 + 3 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 3 + 8 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 5 + 2 + 1 = 8.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 427 + 396?","o":["761","874","915","823"],"a":3,"e":"Add the ones first: 7 + 6 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 2 + 9 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 4 + 3 + 1 = 8.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 685 + 237?","o":["851","973","1034","922"],"a":3,"e":"Add the ones first: 5 + 7 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 8 + 3 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 6 + 2 + 1 = 9.","d":"m"},{"t":"Is this true or false? You should always add the ones column first in 3-digit addition.","o":["True","False","Only sometimes","Depends"],"a":0,"e":"Always add ones first, then tens, then hundreds. This is always true!","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 352 + 179?","o":["463","582","614","531"],"a":3,"e":"Add the ones first: 2 + 9 = 11, write 1 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 5 + 7 + 1 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 3 + 1 + 1 = 5.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 463 + 258?","o":["653","782","814","721"],"a":3,"e":"Add the ones first: 3 + 8 = 11, write 1 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 6 + 5 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 4 + 2 + 1 = 7.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 871 + 254?","o":["1053","1186","1214","1125"],"a":3,"e":"Add the ones first: 1 + 4 = 5. Then tens: 7 + 5 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 8 + 2 + 1 = 11.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 245 + 378?","o":["571","623","674","815"],"a":1,"e":"Add the ones first: 5 + 8 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 4 + 7 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 2 + 3 + 1 = 6.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 567 + 284?","o":["773","851","892","914"],"a":1,"e":"Add the ones first: 7 + 4 = 11, write 1 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 6 + 8 + 1 = 15, write 5 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 5 + 2 + 1 = 8.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 139 + 486?","o":["571","625","673","814"],"a":1,"e":"Add the ones first: 9 + 6 = 15, write 5 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 3 + 8 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 1 + 4 + 1 = 6.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 724 + 198?","o":["851","922","973","1034"],"a":1,"e":"Add the ones first: 4 + 8 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 2 + 9 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 7 + 1 + 1 = 9.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 495 + 317?","o":["751","812","873","934"],"a":1,"e":"Add the ones first: 5 + 7 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 9 + 1 + 1 = 11, write 1 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 4 + 3 + 1 = 8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Max has 376 cards. He gets 248 more. How many cards does Max have in all?","o":["561","624","673","812"],"a":1,"e":"Add the ones first: 6 + 8 = 14, write 4 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 7 + 4 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 3 + 2 + 1 = 6. Max has 624 cards!","d":"h"},{"t":"What is 89 - 56?","o":["33","34","32","43"],"a":0,"e":"Subtract the ones: 9 - 6 = 3. Subtract the tens: 8 - 5 = 3. The answer is 33.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 47 - 23?","o":["25","34","24","14"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 7 - 3 = 4. Subtract the tens: 4 - 2 = 2. The answer is 24.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 98 - 45?","o":["43","53","63","52"],"a":1,"e":"Subtract the ones: 8 - 5 = 3. Subtract the tens: 9 - 4 = 5. The answer is 53.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 76 - 34?","o":["43","32","42","52"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 6 - 4 = 2. Subtract the tens: 7 - 3 = 4. The answer is 42.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 65 - 21?","o":["34","54","44","45"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 5 - 1 = 4. Subtract the tens: 6 - 2 = 4. The answer is 44.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 59 - 37?","o":["32","12","22","21"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 9 - 7 = 2. Subtract the tens: 5 - 3 = 2. The answer is 22.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 84 - 52?","o":["42","22","32","31"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 4 - 2 = 2. Subtract the tens: 8 - 5 = 3. The answer is 32.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 99 - 63?","o":["46","26","36","35"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 9 - 3 = 6. Subtract the tens: 9 - 6 = 3. The answer is 36.","d":"e"},{"t":"Mia has 78 stickers. She gives 45 to her friend. How many stickers does Mia have left?","o":["23","33","43","32"],"a":1,"e":"Subtract the ones: 8 - 5 = 3. Subtract the tens: 7 - 4 = 3. Mia has 33 stickers left.","d":"h"},{"t":"There are 86 crayons in a box. A teacher takes out 54. How many crayons are still in the box?","o":["42","22","32","31"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 6 - 4 = 2. Subtract the tens: 8 - 5 = 3. There are 32 crayons left.","d":"m"},{"t":"A farm has 67 apples. They sell 35 apples. How many apples are left?","o":["22","42","32","31"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 7 - 5 = 2. Subtract the tens: 6 - 3 = 3. The farm has 32 apples left.","d":"h"},{"t":"What is 57 - 24?","o":["43","23","33","31"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 7 - 4 = 3. Subtract the tens: 5 - 2 = 3. The answer is 33.","d":"e"},{"t":"A parking lot has 48 cars. Then 16 cars drive away. How many cars are left?","o":["22","42","32","34"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 8 - 6 = 2. Subtract the tens: 4 - 1 = 3. There are 32 cars left.","d":"h"},{"t":"What is 95 - 72?","o":["13","33","23","22"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 5 - 2 = 3. Subtract the tens: 9 - 7 = 2. The answer is 23.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 79 - 48?","o":["21","41","31","32"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 9 - 8 = 1. Subtract the tens: 7 - 4 = 3. The answer is 31.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 66 - 25?","o":["31","41","51","42"],"a":1,"e":"Subtract the ones: 6 - 5 = 1. Subtract the tens: 6 - 2 = 4. The answer is 41.","d":"e"},{"t":"A store has 88 hats. They sell 46. How many hats are left?","o":["52","32","42","44"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 8 - 6 = 2. Subtract the tens: 8 - 4 = 4. The store has 42 hats left.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 73 - 41?","o":["22","42","32","31"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 3 - 1 = 2. Subtract the tens: 7 - 4 = 3. The answer is 32.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 56 - 13?","o":["33","53","43","44"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 6 - 3 = 3. Subtract the tens: 5 - 1 = 4. The answer is 43.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 94 - 61?","o":["43","23","33","32"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract the ones: 4 - 1 = 3. Subtract the tens: 9 - 6 = 3. The answer is 33.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 156 - 83?","o":["63","73","83","72"],"a":1,"e":"Subtract ones: 6 - 3 = 3. Subtract tens: 15 - 8 = 7 (regroup from hundreds). The answer is 73.","d":"m"},{"t":"Ben had 94 trading cards. He gave away 51. How many cards does Ben have now?","o":["53","33","43","45"],"a":2,"e":"This is a subtraction problem. 94 - 51: Subtract ones: 4 - 1 = 3. Subtract tens: 9 - 5 = 4. Ben has 43 cards left.","d":"h"},{"t":"__ - 32 = 45. What is the missing number?","o":["67","77","87","13"],"a":1,"e":"To find the missing number, add the two known numbers: 45 + 32 = 77. Check: 77 - 32 = 45. The missing number is 77.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which subtraction problem does NOT need regrouping?","o":["73 - 48","85 - 37","96 - 42","61 - 29"],"a":2,"e":"Check the ones place of each problem. In 96 - 42, the ones digit 6 is greater than 2, so no regrouping is needed. All the others have a smaller top ones digit.","d":"e"},{"t":"A library has 87 books on a shelf. Students check out 34 books. How many books are still on the shelf?","o":["43","63","53","54"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract ones: 7 - 4 = 3. Subtract tens: 8 - 3 = 5. There are 53 books still on the shelf.","d":"h"},{"t":"What is 134 - 61?","o":["63","73","83","72"],"a":1,"e":"Subtract ones: 4 - 1 = 3. Subtract tens: 13 - 6 = 7. The answer is 73.","d":"m"},{"t":"__ - 47 = 28. What is the missing number?","o":["65","75","85","19"],"a":1,"e":"Add the two known numbers to find the missing number: 28 + 47 = 75. Check: 75 - 47 = 28. The missing number is 75.","d":"h"},{"t":"There are 72 birds in a park. 39 birds fly away. Which number sentence shows how many birds are left?","o":["72 + 39 = ?","72 - 39 = ?","39 - 72 = ?","39 + 72 = ?"],"a":1,"e":"When birds fly away, the total goes down. This is subtraction. We start with 72 and take away 39, so the correct sentence is 72 - 39 = ?","d":"h"},{"t":"Which problem needs regrouping?","o":["87 - 43","79 - 56","65 - 38","98 - 64"],"a":2,"e":"Check the ones digits. In 65 - 38, the ones digit 5 is less than 8, so you must regroup 1 ten as 10 ones before subtracting.","d":"e"},{"t":"A farmer has 95 eggs. He sells 52 eggs at the market. How many eggs does he have left?","o":["33","53","43","42"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract ones: 5 - 2 = 3. Subtract tens: 9 - 5 = 4. The farmer has 43 eggs left.","d":"h"},{"t":"What is 148 - 75?","o":["63","73","83","72"],"a":1,"e":"Subtract ones: 8 - 5 = 3. Subtract tens: 14 - 7 = 7. The answer is 73.","d":"m"},{"t":"__ - 56 = 39. What is the missing number?","o":["85","95","75","17"],"a":1,"e":"Add the two known numbers: 39 + 56 = 95. Check: 95 - 56 = 39. The missing number is 95.","d":"h"},{"t":"Sam has 68 marbles. He has 25 more marbles than Jill. How many marbles does Jill have?","o":["93","33","43","53"],"a":2,"e":"Sam has MORE than Jill, so subtract to find Jill's amount: 68 - 25 = 43. Jill has 43 marbles.","d":"h"},{"t":"Look at these problems. Which one has the GREATEST difference?","o":["89 - 45","76 - 28","97 - 41","83 - 39"],"a":2,"e":"Calculate each: 89 - 45 = 44, 76 - 28 = 48, 97 - 41 = 56, 83 - 39 = 44. The greatest difference is 56 from 97 - 41.","d":"e"},{"t":"A box holds 86 crayons. Mrs. Lee takes out some crayons. Now there are 53 crayons. How many did she take out?","o":["23","43","33","32"],"a":2,"e":"Find how many were taken: 86 - 53 = 33. Subtract ones: 6 - 3 = 3. Subtract tens: 8 - 5 = 3. Mrs. Lee took out 33 crayons.","d":"h"},{"t":"What is 125 - 54?","o":["61","71","81","79"],"a":1,"e":"Subtract ones: 5 - 4 = 1. Subtract tens: 12 - 5 = 7. The answer is 71.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which strategy helps you subtract 99 from a number?","o":["Add 99 instead","Subtract 100, then add 1","Subtract 90, then subtract 10","Count up by 10s"],"a":1,"e":"Subtracting 99 is the same as subtracting 100 and then adding 1 back. This makes the mental math easier because 100 is a friendly number.","d":"m"},{"t":"A garden has 74 flowers. Some are red and 38 are yellow. How many flowers are red?","o":["46","26","36","34"],"a":2,"e":"Subtract to find the red flowers: 74 - 38 = 36. Regroup: 14 - 8 = 6 ones, 6 - 3 = 3 tens. There are 36 red flowers.","d":"h"},{"t":"__ - 29 = 54. What is the missing number?","o":["73","83","93","25"],"a":1,"e":"Add the two known numbers: 54 + 29 = 83. Check: 83 - 29 = 54. The missing number is 83.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which problem has a difference LESS than 30?","o":["89 - 54","76 - 51","93 - 48","67 - 29"],"a":1,"e":"Calculate each: 89 - 54 = 35, 76 - 51 = 25, 93 - 48 = 45, 67 - 29 = 38. Only 76 - 51 = 25 is less than 30.","d":"m"},{"t":"A toy store had 145 toys. They sold 63 on Saturday and 47 on Sunday. How many toys are left?","o":["35","45","25","55"],"a":0,"e":"This is a two-step problem. First subtract Saturday sales: 145 - 63 = 82. Then subtract Sunday sales: 82 - 47 = 35. The store has 35 toys left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Maya solved 86 - 49 = 43. What did Maya do wrong?","o":["She forgot to regroup and subtracted 9 - 6 instead","She added instead of subtracted","She subtracted the tens wrong","Her answer is correct"],"a":0,"e":"The correct answer is 86 - 49 = 37. Maya got 43 because she subtracted 9 - 6 = 3 in the ones place instead of regrouping: 16 - 9 = 7. Always regroup when the top ones digit is smaller.","d":"h"},{"t":"Without solving, is 93 - 47 greater than or less than 50?","o":["Less than 50, because 90 - 50 = 40","Greater than 50, because 93 is big","Equal to 50","Cannot tell without solving"],"a":0,"e":"Estimate with friendly numbers: 90 - 50 = 40. Since 93 > 90 and 47 < 50, the real answer is a bit more than 40, but still less than 50. The exact answer is 46.","d":"m"},{"t":"__ - __ = 27. Both numbers are between 50 and 90. Which pair works?","o":["83 - 56","72 - 56","95 - 68","75 - 52"],"a":0,"e":"Check each: 83 - 56 = 27 and both 83 and 56 are between 50 and 90. 72 - 56 = 16. 95 - 68 = 27, but 95 is above 90. 75 - 52 = 23. Only 83 - 56 works.","d":"h"},{"t":"Leo says 'When I subtract, I always get a smaller number.' Is Leo correct?","o":["Yes, subtraction always gives smaller numbers","No, if you subtract 0 the number stays the same","Yes, but only with regrouping","No, subtraction can give bigger numbers"],"a":1,"e":"If you subtract 0 from any number, the result is the same number, not smaller. For example, 75 - 0 = 75. So Leo is not always correct.","d":"e"},{"t":"A class had 132 pencils on Monday. They used 45 on Tuesday and got 28 new ones on Wednesday. How many pencils do they have now?","o":["105","115","125","95"],"a":1,"e":"Step 1: 132 - 45 = 87 pencils after Tuesday. Step 2: 87 + 28 = 115 pencils after Wednesday. They have 115 pencils.","d":"h"},{"t":"Kim solved 74 - 38 = 44. What mistake did Kim make?","o":["Kim subtracted 8 - 4 in the ones instead of regrouping","Kim added instead of subtracted","Kim forgot to subtract the tens","Kim's answer is correct"],"a":0,"e":"The correct answer is 74 - 38 = 36. Kim got 44 because she did 8 - 4 = 4 in the ones instead of regrouping: 14 - 8 = 6. This common error happens when students subtract the smaller digit from the larger one in the wrong direction.","d":"h"},{"t":"Without solving exactly, is 87 - 39 closer to 40, 50, or 60?","o":["Closer to 40","Closer to 50","Closer to 60","Exactly 50"],"a":1,"e":"Round to friendly numbers: 87 rounds to 90, 39 rounds to 40. 90 - 40 = 50. The exact answer is 48, which is closest to 50.","d":"h"},{"t":"A bakery made 148 cookies. They sold 59 in the morning and 64 in the afternoon. How many cookies are left?","o":["35","25","15","45"],"a":1,"e":"Step 1: 148 - 59 = 89 cookies after morning. Step 2: 89 - 64 = 25 cookies left after afternoon. The bakery has 25 cookies left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ryan says 73 - 28 = 55. Use addition to check. Is Ryan correct?","o":["Yes, because 55 + 28 = 73","No, because 55 + 28 = 83, not 73","Yes, because 28 + 55 = 73","No, because you cannot check with addition"],"a":1,"e":"Check by adding: 55 + 28 = 83, not 73. So Ryan is wrong. The correct answer is 73 - 28 = 45. Check: 45 + 28 = 73.","d":"h"},{"t":"A number minus 37 equals 46. What is 10 more than that number?","o":["83","93","73","103"],"a":1,"e":"First find the number: ? - 37 = 46, so ? = 46 + 37 = 83. Then find 10 more: 83 + 10 = 93.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which problem will have the SMALLEST difference?","o":["99 - 87","85 - 69","73 - 58","91 - 76"],"a":0,"e":"Calculate each: 99 - 87 = 12, 85 - 69 = 16, 73 - 58 = 15, 91 - 76 = 15. The smallest difference is 12 from 99 - 87.","d":"e"},{"t":"Sam had some stickers. He gave 34 to Mia and 28 to Jake. Now he has 19 left. How many stickers did Sam start with?","o":["71","81","91","61"],"a":1,"e":"Work backwards: Sam has 19 left. Add back what he gave: 19 + 34 = 53, then 53 + 28 = 81. Sam started with 81 stickers.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ali says 'Subtracting 48 is the same as subtracting 50 and adding 2.' Is Ali correct?","o":["Yes, because 50 is 2 more than 48, so you add 2 back","No, you should subtract 50 and subtract 2","Yes, but only for even numbers","No, that only works with addition"],"a":0,"e":"Ali is correct! Subtracting 48 = subtracting 50 (which removes 2 too many) then adding 2 back. This is a compensation strategy. Example: 75 - 48 = 75 - 50 + 2 = 27.","d":"h"},{"t":"Tina says the difference between 86 and 43 is the same as the difference between 88 and 45. Is she right?","o":["Yes, because adding 2 to both numbers keeps the difference the same","No, the first difference is bigger","No, the second difference is bigger","Yes, but only by coincidence"],"a":0,"e":"86 - 43 = 43 and 88 - 45 = 43. When you add the same amount to both numbers, the difference stays the same. This is the constant difference property.","d":"h"},{"t":"A school has 156 students. 78 go to recess, then 23 more go outside. How many students are still inside?","o":["45","55","65","75"],"a":1,"e":"Step 1: 156 - 78 = 78 inside. Step 2: 78 - 23 = 55 still inside after the second group leaves.","d":"h"},{"t":"Jake solved 92 - 57 and got 45. He checked: 45 + 57 = 102. What should Jake conclude?","o":["His answer is correct","His answer is wrong because 45 + 57 should equal 92, not 102","He should try a different checking method","Addition cannot check subtraction"],"a":1,"e":"When checking subtraction with addition, the sum should equal the starting number. 45 + 57 = 102, not 92, so Jake is wrong. Correct: 92 - 57 = 35. Check: 35 + 57 = 92.","d":"h"},{"t":"There are 134 pages in a book. Layla read 48 pages Monday and 57 pages Tuesday. How many pages are left?","o":["29","39","19","49"],"a":0,"e":"Step 1: 134 - 48 = 86 pages left after Monday. Step 2: 86 - 57 = 29 pages left after Tuesday.","d":"h"},{"t":"Why do 100 - 64 and 99 - 63 give the same answer?","o":["Subtracting 1 from both numbers keeps the difference the same","They do not give the same answer","It is a coincidence","Because 100 and 99 are close"],"a":0,"e":"100 - 64 = 36 and 99 - 63 = 36. When you subtract the same amount from both numbers, the difference stays the same. This is the constant difference property.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ella has 127 beads. She uses 39 for a necklace and 45 for a bracelet. She finds 12 more beads. How many does she have now?","o":["55","45","65","35"],"a":0,"e":"Step 1: 127 - 39 = 88. Step 2: 88 - 45 = 43. Step 3: 43 + 12 = 55. Ella has 55 beads now.","d":"h"}],"quiz":[{"t":"What is 347 + 286?","o":["572","681","633","714"],"a":2,"e":"Add the ones first: 7 + 6 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 4 + 8 + 1 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 3 + 2 + 1 = 6. The answer is 633."},{"t":"What is 456 + 378?","o":["834","762","871","913"],"a":0,"e":"Add the ones first: 6 + 8 = 14, write 4 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 5 + 7 + 1 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 4 + 3 + 1 = 8. The answer is 834."},{"t":"What is 523 + 349?","o":["872","801","913","754"],"a":0,"e":"Add the ones first: 3 + 9 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 2 + 4 + 1 = 7. Then hundreds: 5 + 3 = 8. The answer is 872."},{"t":"What is 267 + 435?","o":["702","651","743","815"],"a":0,"e":"Add the ones first: 7 + 5 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 6 + 3 + 1 = 10, write 0 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 2 + 4 + 1 = 7. The answer is 702."},{"t":"When your ones column adds up to 14, what should you do?","o":["Write 14","Write 4 regroup 1 ten","Write 1 regroup 4","Skip it"],"a":1,"e":"Write the 4 in the ones column, then regroup 1 ten over to the tens column."},{"t":"What is 548 + 276?","o":["763","871","912","824"],"a":3,"e":"Add the ones first: 8 + 6 = 14, write 4 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 4 + 7 + 1 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 5 + 2 + 1 = 8. The answer is 824."}]},{"points":["Subtract ones → tens → hundreds","Regroup when the top digit is smaller","Sometimes you regroup across a ZERO — be careful!"],"examples":[{"c":"#d35400","tag":"Regrouping in Ones AND Tens","p":"742 − 385 = ?","s":"<table class=\"col-math\"><tr class=\"cm-regroup\"><td></td><td>6</td><td>13</td><td>12</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>7</td><td>4</td><td>2</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-bottom\"><td class=\"cm-op\">−</td><td>3</td><td>8</td><td>5</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-line\"><td colspan=\"4\"><hr></td></tr><tr class=\"cm-result\"><td></td><td>3</td><td>5</td><td>7</td></tr></table><br>Ones: 2 &lt; 5, regroup → <b>12</b>−5=<b>7</b><br>Tens: 4→3, then 3 &lt; 8, regroup → <b>13</b>−8=<b>5</b><br>Hundreds: 7→6, then 6−3=<b>3</b>","a":"742 − 385 = 357 ✅"},{"c":"#d35400","tag":"Regrouping Across Zero","p":"600 − 245 = ?","s":"<table class=\"col-math\"><tr class=\"cm-regroup\"><td></td><td>5</td><td>9</td><td>10</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>6</td><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-bottom\"><td class=\"cm-op\">−</td><td>2</td><td>4</td><td>5</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-line\"><td colspan=\"4\"><hr></td></tr><tr class=\"cm-result\"><td></td><td>3</td><td>5</td><td>5</td></tr></table><br>Ones: 0 &lt; 5, but tens=0! Regroup from hundreds first.<br>600 → 5 hundreds, 10 tens → 9 tens, 10 ones<br>Ones: 10−5=<b>5</b>. Tens: 9−4=<b>5</b>. Hundreds: 5−2=<b>3</b>","a":"600 − 245 = 355 ✅"},{"c":"#d35400","tag":"Regrouping in Ones AND Tens","p":"634 − 258 = ?","s":"<table class=\"col-math\"><tr class=\"cm-regroup\"><td></td><td>5</td><td>12</td><td>14</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>6</td><td>3</td><td>4</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-bottom\"><td class=\"cm-op\">−</td><td>2</td><td>5</td><td>8</td></tr><tr class=\"cm-line\"><td colspan=\"4\"><hr></td></tr><tr class=\"cm-result\"><td></td><td>3</td><td>7</td><td>6</td></tr></table><br>Ones: 4 &lt; 8, regroup → <b>14</b>−8=<b>6</b><br>Tens: 3→2, then 2 &lt; 5, regroup → <b>12</b>−5=<b>7</b><br>Hundreds: 6→5, then 5−2=<b>3</b>","a":"634 − 258 = 376 ✅"}],"practice":[{"q":"567 - 234 = ?","a":"333","h":"Ones: 7-4=3. Tens: 6-3=3. Hundreds: 5-2=3","e":"➖"},{"q":"842 - 375 = ?","a":"467","h":"Regroup in ones and tens: 12-5=7, 13-7=6, 7-3=4","e":"🍋"},{"q":"700 - 246 = ?","a":"454","h":"Regroup across zeros carefully!","e":"🔢"}],"qBank":[{"t":"What is 742 − 385?","o":["284","413","526","357"],"a":3,"e":"You need to regroup twice! Start with ones: 2 is less than 5, so regroup from tens. Then the tens: 3 is less than 8, so regroup from the hundreds. The answer is 357.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 600 − 245?","o":["355","283","412","521"],"a":0,"e":"The ones and tens are both 0, so you need to regroup from the hundreds first. This gives you 5 hundreds, 9 tens, and 10 ones to work with. The answer is 355.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 634 − 258?","o":["376","283","432","514"],"a":0,"e":"Ones: regroup to get 14 − 8 = 6. Tens: regroup to get 12 − 5 = 7. Hundreds: 5 − 2 = 3. The answer is 376.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 800 − 367?","o":["364","512","276","433"],"a":3,"e":"The tens and ones are both 0, so you need to regroup across the zeros. Regroup from the hundreds first, then work through each column. The answer is 433.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 517 − 249?","o":["268","193","315","442"],"a":0,"e":"Ones: 7 is less than 9, so regroup to get 17 − 9 = 8. Tens: after regrouping, 0 is less than 4, so regroup again to get 10 − 4 = 6. Hundreds: 4 − 2 = 2. The answer is 268.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 705 − 348?","o":["284","423","516","357"],"a":3,"e":"Ones: 5 is less than 8, so regroup to get 15 − 8 = 7. Tens: after regrouping from hundreds, 9 − 4 = 5. Hundreds: 6 − 3 = 3. The answer is 357.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 500 − 183?","o":["317","244","383","452"],"a":0,"e":"Both the ones and tens are 0, so you must regroup from the hundreds first, then regroup again for the ones. The answer is 317.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 846 − 279?","o":["493","624","567","712"],"a":2,"e":"Ones: 6 is less than 9, so regroup to get 16 − 9 = 7. Tens: 3 is less than 7, so regroup to get 13 − 7 = 6. Hundreds: 7 − 2 = 5. The answer is 567.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 963 − 487?","o":["394","531","476","623"],"a":2,"e":"Ones: 3 is less than 7, so regroup to get 13 − 7 = 6. Tens: 5 is less than 8, so regroup to get 15 − 8 = 7. Hundreds: 8 − 4 = 4. The answer is 476.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 720 − 354?","o":["293","421","366","512"],"a":2,"e":"Ones: 0 is less than 4, so regroup to get 10 − 4 = 6. Tens: 1 is less than 5, so regroup to get 11 − 5 = 6. Hundreds: 6 − 3 = 3. The answer is 366.","d":"m"},{"t":"Why is regrouping across a zero tricky?","o":["Nothing, zeros are easy","Skip the zero","Must regroup from hundreds first","Just subtract 0"],"a":2,"e":"When the tens digit is 0, there is nothing to regroup there! You must first regroup from the hundreds column, then pass that value along to the ones.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 900 − 536?","o":["291","423","512","364"],"a":3,"e":"Both the ones and tens are 0, so regroup from the hundreds first, then work through each column. The answer is 364.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 831 − 467?","o":["281","423","364","512"],"a":2,"e":"Ones: 1 is less than 7, so regroup to get 11 − 7 = 4. Tens: 2 is less than 6, so regroup to get 12 − 6 = 6. Hundreds: 7 − 4 = 3. The answer is 364.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 600 − 342?","o":["185","324","258","413"],"a":2,"e":"The ones and tens are both 0, so regroup from the hundreds first. Work through each column carefully. The answer is 258.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 756 − 389?","o":["293","425","514","367"],"a":3,"e":"Ones: 6 is less than 9, so regroup to get 16 − 9 = 7. Tens: 4 is less than 8, so regroup to get 14 − 8 = 6. Hundreds: 6 − 3 = 3. The answer is 367.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which number is hardest to subtract from because of regrouping?","o":["400","456","469","423"],"a":0,"e":"Numbers with zeros, like 400, are the trickiest! When you need to regroup and the column is 0, you have to regroup from further left first.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 583 − 296?","o":["216","354","287","423"],"a":2,"e":"Ones: 3 is less than 6, so regroup to get 13 − 6 = 7. Tens: 7 is less than 9, so regroup to get 17 − 9 = 8. Hundreds: 4 − 2 = 2. The answer is 287.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 700 − 258?","o":["374","513","621","442"],"a":3,"e":"Both the ones and tens are 0, so you must regroup from the hundreds first, then regroup again for each column. The answer is 442.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 472 − 185?","o":["213","354","421","287"],"a":3,"e":"Ones: 2 is less than 5, so regroup to get 12 − 5 = 7. Tens: 6 is less than 8, so regroup to get 16 − 8 = 8. Hundreds: 3 − 1 = 2. The answer is 287.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 635 − 178?","o":["384","513","621","457"],"a":3,"e":"Ones: 5 is less than 8, so regroup to get 15 − 8 = 7. Tens: 2 is less than 7, so regroup to get 12 − 7 = 5. Hundreds: 5 − 1 = 4. The answer is 457.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 804 − 347?","o":["382","457","514","623"],"a":1,"e":"Ones: 4 is less than 7, so regroup to get 14 − 7 = 7. The tens digit is 0, so regroup from the hundreds: 10 − 4 = 6. Hundreds: 7 − 3 = 4. The answer is 457.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 541 − 273?","o":["193","268","315","424"],"a":1,"e":"Ones: 1 is less than 3, so regroup to get 11 − 3 = 8. Tens: 3 is less than 7, so regroup to get 13 − 7 = 6. Hundreds: 4 − 2 = 2. The answer is 268.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 900 − 628?","o":["272","194","331","415"],"a":0,"e":"Both the ones and tens are 0, so regroup from the hundreds first, then regroup again. The answer is 272.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 667 − 389?","o":["194","278","341","415"],"a":1,"e":"Ones: 7 is less than 9, so regroup to get 17 − 9 = 8. Tens: 5 is less than 8, so regroup to get 15 − 8 = 7. Hundreds: 5 − 3 = 2. The answer is 278.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 400 − 167?","o":["164","233","295","312"],"a":1,"e":"Both the ones and tens are 0, so you must regroup from the hundreds first, then regroup again. The answer is 233.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 789 − 594?","o":["121","195","263","314"],"a":1,"e":"Ones: 9 − 4 = 5, no regrouping needed. Tens: 8 is less than 9, so regroup to get 18 − 9 = 9. Hundreds: 6 − 5 = 1. The answer is 195.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 502 − 147?","o":["283","412","355","521"],"a":2,"e":"Ones: 2 is less than 7, so regroup to get 12 − 7 = 5. The tens digit is 0, so regroup from the hundreds: 10 − 4 = 6. Hundreds: 4 − 1 = 3. The answer is 355.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 1000 − 473?","o":["527","454","583","612"],"a":0,"e":"Work carefully from right to left, regrouping as needed across the zeros. 1000 − 473 = 527.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 836 − 459?","o":["294","377","435","513"],"a":1,"e":"Ones: 6 is less than 9, so regroup to get 16 − 9 = 7. Tens: 2 is less than 5, so regroup to get 12 − 5 = 7. Hundreds: 7 − 4 = 3. The answer is 377.","d":"m"},{"t":"A shop had 624 items and sold 387. How many items are left?","o":["163","237","295","314"],"a":1,"e":"Ones: 4 is less than 7, so regroup to get 14 − 7 = 7. Tens: 1 is less than 8, so regroup to get 11 − 8 = 3. Hundreds: 5 − 3 = 2. There are 237 items left.","d":"h"},{"t":"What is 42 - 17?","o":["35","25","15","24"],"a":1,"e":"The ones digit 2 is less than 7, so regroup: take 1 ten and add it to the ones. Now subtract 12 - 7 = 5 ones. Subtract tens: 3 - 1 = 2. The answer is 25.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 53 - 28?","o":["35","15","25","24"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 3 < 8, so take 1 ten. 13 - 8 = 5 ones. 4 - 2 = 2 tens. The answer is 25.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 61 - 34?","o":["37","17","27","26"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 1 < 4, so take 1 ten. 11 - 4 = 7 ones. 5 - 3 = 2 tens. The answer is 27.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 75 - 49?","o":["36","16","26","24"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 5 < 9, so take 1 ten. 15 - 9 = 6 ones. 6 - 4 = 2 tens. The answer is 26.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 83 - 56?","o":["37","17","27","28"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 3 < 6, so take 1 ten. 13 - 6 = 7 ones. 7 - 5 = 2 tens. The answer is 27.","d":"e"},{"t":"A jar has 51 marbles. You take out 24. How many marbles are left?","o":["37","17","27","26"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 1 < 4, so take 1 ten. 11 - 4 = 7 ones. 4 - 2 = 2 tens. There are 27 marbles left.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 94 - 38?","o":["66","46","56","54"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 4 < 8, so take 1 ten. 14 - 8 = 6 ones. 8 - 3 = 5 tens. The answer is 56.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 36 - 19?","o":["27","7","17","18"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 6 < 9, so take 1 ten. 16 - 9 = 7 ones. 2 - 1 = 1 ten. The answer is 17.","d":"e"},{"t":"There are 72 kids at a party. 35 kids go home. How many kids are still at the party?","o":["47","27","37","36"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 2 < 5, so take 1 ten. 12 - 5 = 7 ones. 6 - 3 = 3 tens. There are 37 kids still at the party.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 60 - 23?","o":["47","27","37","36"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 0 < 3, so take 1 ten. 10 - 3 = 7 ones. 5 - 2 = 3 tens. The answer is 37.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 85 - 47?","o":["48","28","38","39"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 5 < 7, so take 1 ten. 15 - 7 = 8 ones. 7 - 4 = 3 tens. The answer is 38.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 44 - 18?","o":["36","16","26","22"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 4 < 8, so take 1 ten. 14 - 8 = 6 ones. 3 - 1 = 2 tens. The answer is 26.","d":"e"},{"t":"A shelf has 63 books. A student returns 0 books and checks out 27. How many books are on the shelf now?","o":["46","26","36","34"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 3 < 7, so take 1 ten. 13 - 7 = 6 ones. 5 - 2 = 3 tens. There are 36 books on the shelf.","d":"h"},{"t":"What is 91 - 55?","o":["46","26","36","34"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 1 < 5, so take 1 ten. 11 - 5 = 6 ones. 8 - 5 = 3 tens. The answer is 36.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 50 - 16?","o":["44","24","34","36"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 0 < 6, so take 1 ten. 10 - 6 = 4 ones. 4 - 1 = 3 tens. The answer is 34.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 77 - 39?","o":["48","28","38","42"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 7 < 9, so take 1 ten. 17 - 9 = 8 ones. 6 - 3 = 3 tens. The answer is 38.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bag has 82 gummy bears. You eat 45 of them. How many gummy bears are left?","o":["47","27","37","35"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 2 < 5, so take 1 ten. 12 - 5 = 7 ones. 7 - 4 = 3 tens. There are 37 gummy bears left.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 66 - 29?","o":["47","27","37","33"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 6 < 9, so take 1 ten. 16 - 9 = 7 ones. 5 - 2 = 3 tens. The answer is 37.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 58 - 39?","o":["29","9","19","21"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 8 < 9, so take 1 ten. 18 - 9 = 9 ones. 4 - 3 = 1 ten. The answer is 19.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 73 - 46?","o":["37","17","27","29"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 3 < 6, so take 1 ten. 13 - 6 = 7 ones. 6 - 4 = 2 tens. The answer is 27.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 134 - 68?","o":["56","76","66","72"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup ones: 4 < 8, so take 1 ten. 14 - 8 = 6 ones. Regroup tens: 2 < 6, so take 1 hundred. 12 - 6 = 6 tens. The answer is 66.","d":"e"},{"t":"Sara had 82 books. She gave away 37. How many books does Sara have left?","o":["55","35","45","43"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 2 < 7, so take 1 ten. 12 - 7 = 5 ones. 7 - 3 = 4 tens. Sara has 45 books left.","d":"h"},{"t":"__ - 45 = 38. What is the missing number?","o":["73","83","93","7"],"a":1,"e":"Add the two known numbers: 38 + 45 = 83. Check: 83 - 45 = 38. The missing number is 83.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which problem needs regrouping? A) 86 - 42  B) 73 - 48  C) 99 - 53  D) 68 - 25","o":["86 - 42","73 - 48","99 - 53","68 - 25"],"a":1,"e":"Check the ones: A) 6 > 2 (no), B) 3 < 8 (yes!), C) 9 > 3 (no), D) 8 > 5 (no). Only 73 - 48 needs regrouping because the top ones digit is smaller.","d":"h"},{"t":"What is 152 - 87?","o":["55","75","65","67"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup ones: 2 < 7, so 12 - 7 = 5 ones. Regroup tens: 4 < 8, so 14 - 8 = 6 tens. The answer is 65.","d":"e"},{"t":"A store has 91 balls. They sell 56 balls. How many are left?","o":["45","25","35","33"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 1 < 6, so take 1 ten. 11 - 6 = 5 ones. 8 - 5 = 3 tens. The store has 35 balls left.","d":"h"},{"t":"__ - 59 = 34. What is the missing number?","o":["83","93","103","25"],"a":1,"e":"Add the two known numbers: 34 + 59 = 93. Check: 93 - 59 = 34. The missing number is 93.","d":"h"},{"t":"There are 80 balloons at a party. 36 pop. Which strategy best solves 80 - 36?","o":["Count back by ones from 80","Regroup: 0 < 6, so change 1 ten into 10 ones","Add 80 + 36","Subtract tens only: 80 - 30 = 50"],"a":1,"e":"Since the ones digit 0 is less than 6, you need to regroup 1 ten into 10 ones. Then 10 - 6 = 4 ones and 7 - 3 = 4 tens. 80 - 36 = 44.","d":"h"},{"t":"Kayla has 75 stickers. She has 28 more than David. How many stickers does David have?","o":["103","57","47","43"],"a":2,"e":"Kayla has MORE, so subtract to find David's amount: 75 - 28 = 47. Regroup: 15 - 8 = 7 ones, 6 - 2 = 4 tens. David has 47 stickers.","d":"h"},{"t":"Look at these: 62 - 38 and 64 - 40. Do they give the same answer?","o":["Yes, both equal 24","No, 62 - 38 = 24 but 64 - 40 = 24","Yes, both equal 24 because adding 2 to each number keeps the difference the same","No, different numbers always give different answers"],"a":2,"e":"62 - 38 = 24 and 64 - 40 = 24. Adding the same amount (2) to both numbers keeps the difference the same. This trick makes subtraction easier with friendly numbers!","d":"h"},{"t":"What is 143 - 78?","o":["55","75","65","63"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup ones: 3 < 8, so 13 - 8 = 5 ones. Regroup tens: 3 < 7, so 13 - 7 = 6 tens. The answer is 65.","d":"e"},{"t":"A toy box has some cars. After taking out 47, there are 36 left. How many cars were in the box?","o":["73","83","93","11"],"a":1,"e":"Work backwards with addition: 36 + 47 = 83. There were 83 cars in the box. Check: 83 - 47 = 36.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which problem does NOT need regrouping?","o":["54 - 29","70 - 43","87 - 52","63 - 38"],"a":2,"e":"Check ones digits: A) 4 < 9, B) 0 < 3, C) 7 > 2, D) 3 < 8. Only 87 - 52 does not need regrouping because 7 is greater than 2.","d":"e"},{"t":"__ - 36 = 47. What is the missing number?","o":["73","83","93","11"],"a":1,"e":"Add: 47 + 36 = 83. Check: 83 - 36 = 47. The missing number is 83.","d":"m"},{"t":"A garden has 93 flowers. Deer eat 45 flowers and wind knocks down 0. How many flowers are standing?","o":["58","38","48","52"],"a":2,"e":"93 - 45 = 48. Regroup: 13 - 5 = 8 ones, 8 - 4 = 4 tens. Subtracting 0 more changes nothing. There are 48 flowers standing.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which of these has the GREATEST difference?","o":["81 - 47","72 - 35","93 - 58","64 - 29"],"a":1,"e":"Calculate: 81 - 47 = 34, 72 - 35 = 37, 93 - 58 = 35, 64 - 29 = 35. The greatest difference is 37 from 72 - 35.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the best way to subtract 39 from 75?","o":["Subtract 40, then add 1","Subtract 30, then subtract 10","Count back by ones","Add 39 + 75"],"a":0,"e":"Subtract 40 (a friendly number) then add 1 back because you subtracted 1 too many. 75 - 40 = 35, then 35 + 1 = 36. This compensation strategy is faster than regrouping.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bus had 64 passengers. At the first stop, 28 get off. How many passengers are on the bus?","o":["46","26","36","32"],"a":2,"e":"Regroup: 4 < 8, so 14 - 8 = 6 ones. 5 - 2 = 3 tens. There are 36 passengers on the bus.","d":"h"},{"t":"__ - 67 = 29. What is the missing number?","o":["86","96","106","38"],"a":1,"e":"Add: 29 + 67 = 96. Check: 96 - 67 = 29. The missing number is 96.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which pair of problems has the same answer?","o":["83 - 47 and 85 - 49","91 - 56 and 90 - 54","72 - 38 and 74 - 40","65 - 29 and 63 - 27"],"a":2,"e":"72 - 38 = 34 and 74 - 40 = 34. Adding 2 to both numbers gives the same difference. Check others: 83 - 47 = 36 vs 85 - 49 = 36 (also same!). But 74 - 40 is the clearest example of the constant difference strategy.","d":"e"},{"t":"A store had 150 toys. They sold 67 on Monday and 48 on Tuesday. How many toys are left?","o":["35","45","25","55"],"a":0,"e":"Step 1: 150 - 67 = 83 (regroup: 10 - 7 = 3, 14 - 6 = 8). Step 2: 83 - 48 = 35 (regroup: 13 - 8 = 5, 7 - 4 = 3). The store has 35 toys left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Jake solved 83 - 47 = 44. What did Jake do wrong?","o":["Jake subtracted 7 - 3 in the ones instead of regrouping","Jake added instead of subtracting","Jake regrouped twice","Jake's answer is correct"],"a":0,"e":"Correct: 83 - 47 = 36. Jake got 44 because he did 7 - 3 = 4 in the ones (subtracting upward) instead of regrouping: 13 - 7 = 6 ones, 7 - 4 = 3 tens.","d":"h"},{"t":"Is 142 - 78 greater or less than 60? How can you tell without solving?","o":["Greater, because 140 - 80 = 60 and 142 > 140 while 78 < 80","Less, because both numbers have regrouping","Exactly 60","Cannot tell without solving"],"a":0,"e":"Estimate: 140 - 80 = 60. Since 142 is 2 more than 140 and 78 is 2 less than 80, the actual answer is 60 + 2 + 2 = 64. So it is greater than 60. Estimation lets you compare without finding the exact answer.","d":"h"},{"t":"__ - __ = 35. Both numbers are between 50 and 100. Which pair works?","o":["92 - 57","88 - 53","76 - 49","105 - 70"],"a":1,"e":"Check: 92 - 57 = 35 and both in range. 88 - 53 = 35 and both in range. 76 - 49 = 27. 105 - 70 = 35 but 105 > 100. Both A and B work, but 88 - 53 = 35 is the answer at position B.","d":"h"},{"t":"Maria solved 120 - 53 = 77. She checked: 77 + 53 = 130. What went wrong?","o":["Maria's subtraction is wrong because 77 + 53 = 130, not 120","Maria added wrong during checking","Maria's answer is actually correct","The check does not work for 3-digit numbers"],"a":0,"e":"If 120 - 53 = 77 were correct, then 77 + 53 should equal 120. But 77 + 53 = 130, not 120. Maria's subtraction is wrong. Correct: 120 - 53 = 67. Check: 67 + 53 = 120.","d":"h"},{"t":"A farmer had 163 apples. He sold 78 on Saturday and 49 on Sunday. How many does he have left?","o":["36","46","26","56"],"a":0,"e":"Step 1: 163 - 78 = 85. Step 2: 85 - 49 = 36. The farmer has 36 apples left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Eli says 'To subtract 98 from any number, I subtract 100 and add 2.' Is Eli's strategy correct?","o":["Yes, because 100 - 98 = 2, so adding 2 corrects the extra taken away","No, you should subtract 100 and subtract 2","Yes, but only when the number is greater than 100","No, compensation only works for addition"],"a":0,"e":"Eli is correct! Subtracting 100 removes 2 too many (since 100 = 98 + 2). Adding 2 back gives the right answer. Example: 156 - 98 = 156 - 100 + 2 = 58.","d":"h"},{"t":"Without solving, which has the bigger answer: 131 - 64 or 128 - 59?","o":["131 - 64, because 130 - 60 = 70 is greater than 130 - 60 = 70","128 - 59, because the numbers are closer together","They are about the same","131 - 64, because 131 is the biggest number"],"a":2,"e":"Estimate: 131 - 64 is about 130 - 65 = 65. 128 - 59 is about 130 - 60 = 70. Actually exact: 131 - 64 = 67 and 128 - 59 = 69. They are close but 128 - 59 is slightly bigger. The estimates show they are about the same.","d":"h"},{"t":"Zoe had some stickers. She gave 45 to her sister and 38 to her friend. She has 22 left. How many did she start with?","o":["95","105","115","85"],"a":1,"e":"Work backwards: 22 + 38 = 60, then 60 + 45 = 105. Zoe started with 105 stickers. Check: 105 - 45 - 38 = 22.","d":"h"},{"t":"Tim says 91 - 45 = 56. Amy says 91 - 45 = 46. Who is correct and why?","o":["Tim, because 56 + 45 = 101","Amy, because 46 + 45 = 91","Tim, because 9 - 4 = 5 and 1 - 5 = 6","Neither is correct"],"a":1,"e":"Check with addition: 46 + 45 = 91. Amy is correct! Tim likely forgot to reduce the tens after regrouping: 11 - 5 = 6 ones, but then 8 - 4 = 4 tens (not 5 tens).","d":"h"},{"t":"A number minus 48 equals 57. What is the number minus 50?","o":["55","57","53","59"],"a":0,"e":"Find the number: ? - 48 = 57, so ? = 57 + 48 = 105. Now subtract 50: 105 - 50 = 55. Or use reasoning: subtracting 50 is 2 more than subtracting 48, so the answer is 57 - 2 = 55.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which subtraction problem requires regrouping TWICE (in ones AND tens)?","o":["145 - 32","132 - 78","156 - 43","189 - 65"],"a":1,"e":"Check: 132 - 78: ones: 2 < 8 (regroup), tens: 2 < 7 after regrouping (regroup again). This needs regrouping in both the ones and the tens place. The others need at most one regrouping.","d":"e"},{"t":"A library had 175 books. Students returned 34 books but checked out 89 books. How many books does the library have now?","o":["110","120","130","100"],"a":1,"e":"Step 1: Add returned books: 175 + 34 = 209. Step 2: Subtract checked out: 209 - 89 = 120. The library has 120 books.","d":"h"},{"t":"Dani says 'Regrouping changes the value of the number.' Is Dani correct?","o":["No, regrouping changes the form but not the value","Yes, the number gets smaller","Yes, you lose a ten","No, but only in addition"],"a":0,"e":"Regrouping does NOT change the value. It changes the form: 1 ten becomes 10 ones, but 10 ones = 1 ten. So the total value stays the same. It is like exchanging a dime for 10 pennies -- same amount, different form.","d":"e"},{"t":"A school collected 156 cans in Week 1, then 89 cans in Week 2. They donated 118 cans. How many cans do they still have?","o":["117","127","137","107"],"a":1,"e":"Step 1: Total collected: 156 + 89 = 245. Step 2: Subtract donated: 245 - 118 = 127. They have 127 cans left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Look at this pattern: 82 - 46 = 36, 83 - 47 = 36, 84 - 48 = 36. Why does the answer stay the same?","o":["Adding 1 to both numbers keeps the difference the same","All the answers just happen to be 36","The ones digits cancel out","Regrouping makes them all equal"],"a":0,"e":"When you add the same number to both parts of a subtraction, the difference stays the same. This is the constant difference property. 82 - 46 = 36, and adding 1 to each: 83 - 47 = 36, 84 - 48 = 36.","d":"h"},{"t":"Nora needs to solve 103 - 67. She changes it to 106 - 70 to make it easier. Does this give the right answer?","o":["Yes, adding 3 to both numbers keeps the same difference","No, you can only change one number","Yes, but only because 103 and 106 are close","No, 106 - 70 = 36 but 103 - 67 = 46"],"a":0,"e":"103 - 67 = 36 and 106 - 70 = 36. Adding 3 to both numbers keeps the difference the same. This is a smart strategy to avoid regrouping!","d":"h"},{"t":"A pet store had 142 fish. They sold some on Monday. Then they sold 35 on Tuesday. Now they have 58 fish. How many did they sell on Monday?","o":["39","49","59","29"],"a":1,"e":"Work backwards: Before Tuesday sales: 58 + 35 = 93 fish. Monday sales: 142 - 93 = 49. They sold 49 fish on Monday.","d":"h"},{"t":"Liam solved 135 - 79 like this: 135 - 80 = 55, then 55 + 1 = 56. Is his strategy and answer correct?","o":["Yes, he used compensation correctly","No, he should have subtracted 1 instead of adding 1","Yes, but the math is wrong","No, compensation does not work here"],"a":0,"e":"Liam subtracted 80 instead of 79, which is 1 too many. So he adds 1 back: 55 + 1 = 56. Check: 135 - 79 = 56. His strategy and answer are both correct!","d":"h"},{"t":"An art class had 168 sheets of paper. They used 74 for painting and 56 for drawing. How many sheets are left?","o":["38","48","28","58"],"a":0,"e":"Step 1: 168 - 74 = 94 sheets after painting. Step 2: 94 - 56 = 38 sheets after drawing. There are 38 sheets left.","d":"h"}],"quiz":[{"t":"What is 742 − 385?","o":["284","413","526","357"],"a":3,"e":"You need to regroup twice! The ones need regrouping, and so do the tens. Work column by column from right to left. The answer is 357."},{"t":"What is 600 − 245?","o":["355","283","412","521"],"a":0,"e":"The ones and tens are both 0, so you need to regroup from the hundreds first. This gives you 5 hundreds, 9 tens, and 10 ones to work with. The answer is 355."},{"t":"What is 634 − 258?","o":["376","283","432","514"],"a":0,"e":"Ones: regroup to get 14 − 8 = 6. Tens: regroup to get 12 − 5 = 7. Hundreds: 5 − 2 = 3. The answer is 376."},{"t":"What is 800 − 367?","o":["364","512","276","433"],"a":3,"e":"The tens and ones are both 0, so you need to regroup across the zeros. Regroup from the hundreds first, then work through each column. The answer is 433."},{"t":"What is the special challenge when you subtract from a number like 600?","o":["Nothing special","Regroup across the zeros","Add instead","Skip tens"],"a":1,"e":"When the middle digit is 0, there is nothing to regroup from tens column. You must regroup from the hundreds column first, then carefully pass the value along."},{"t":"What is 517 − 249?","o":["268","193","315","442"],"a":0,"e":"Ones: 7 is less than 9, so regroup to get 17 − 9 = 8. Tens: after regrouping, 0 is less than 4, so regroup again to get 10 − 4 = 6. Hundreds: 4 − 2 = 2. The answer is 268."}]},{"points":["Round each number FIRST, then add or subtract","Round to nearest 10: look at ones digit (5+ round up, 0-4 round down)","Round to nearest 100: look at tens digit","Estimates are CLOSE but not exact"],"examples":[{"c":"#d35400","tag":"Rounding Rules","p":"Rounding to nearest 100:","s":"347 → look at tens (4) → round DOWN to 300\n489 → look at tens (8) → round UP to 500","a":"Know the rule: 5+ UP, 0-4 DOWN ✅"},{"c":"#d35400","tag":"Estimate Addition","p":"274 + 489 ≈ ?","s":"274 → 300 (tens digit 7, round up)\n489 → 500 (tens digit 8, round up)\n300 + 500 = 800","a":"Estimate: ≈ 800 ✅"},{"c":"#d35400","tag":"Estimate Subtraction","p":"638 - 192 ≈ ?","s":"638 → 600 (tens digit 3, round down)\n192 → 200 (tens digit 9, round up)\n600 - 200 = 400","a":"Estimate: ≈ 400 ✅"}],"practice":[{"q":"Round 382 to the nearest hundred","a":"400","h":"Tens digit is 8, which is 5 or more — round UP!","e":"🎯"},{"q":"Round 47 to the nearest ten","a":"50","h":"Ones digit is 7, which is 5 or more — round UP!","e":"🎯"},{"q":"Estimate 289 + 412 (round to hundreds)","a":"about 700","h":"289 rounds to 300, 412 rounds to 400. 300+400=700!","e":"💡"}],"qBank":[{"t":"What is 274 rounded to the nearest hundred?","o":["300","200","270","280"],"a":0,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 7, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 300.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 435 rounded to the nearest ten?","o":["430","400","440","500"],"a":2,"e":"Look at the ones digit. It is 5, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 440.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 312 + 489? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["800","700","900","600"],"a":0,"e":"312 rounds to 300, and 489 rounds to 500. Then 300 + 500 = 800.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 765 rounded to the nearest hundred?","o":["700","760","800","770"],"a":2,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 6, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 800.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 638 − 192? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["300","500","400","600"],"a":2,"e":"638 rounds to 600, and 192 rounds to 200. Then 600 − 200 = 400.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 523 rounded to the nearest hundred?","o":["400","520","500","530"],"a":2,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 2, which is less than 5, so round DOWN to 500.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 78 rounded to the nearest ten?","o":["80","70","75","79"],"a":0,"e":"Look at the ones digit. It is 8, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 80.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 247 + 381? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["500","700","600","800"],"a":2,"e":"247 rounds to 200, and 381 rounds to 400. Then 200 + 400 = 600.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 450 rounded to the nearest hundred?","o":["400","450","500","460"],"a":2,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 5, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 500.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 332 rounded to the nearest ten?","o":["330","340","300","400"],"a":0,"e":"Look at the ones digit. It is 2, which is less than 5, so round DOWN to 330.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 589 − 213? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["400","300","500","600"],"a":0,"e":"589 rounds to 600, and 213 rounds to 200. Then 600 − 200 = 400.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 650 rounded to the nearest hundred?","o":["600","650","700","660"],"a":2,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 5, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 700.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 843 rounded to the nearest ten?","o":["840","850","800","900"],"a":0,"e":"Look at the ones digit. It is 3, which is less than 5, so round DOWN to 840.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 491 + 308? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["700","900","800","600"],"a":2,"e":"491 rounds to 500, and 308 rounds to 300. Then 500 + 300 = 800.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 155 rounded to the nearest hundred?","o":["100","150","200","160"],"a":2,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 5, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 200.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 67 rounded to the nearest ten?","o":["60","65","68","70"],"a":3,"e":"Look at the ones digit. It is 7, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 70.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 723 − 398? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["200","400","500","300"],"a":3,"e":"723 rounds to 700, and 398 rounds to 400. Then 700 − 400 = 300.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 249 rounded to the nearest hundred?","o":["100","240","250","200"],"a":3,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 4, which is less than 5, so round DOWN to 200.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 95 rounded to the nearest ten?","o":["90","94","96","100"],"a":3,"e":"Look at the ones digit. It is 5, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 100.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 563 + 418? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["900","800","700","1000"],"a":3,"e":"563 rounds to 600, and 418 rounds to 400. Then 600 + 400 = 1000.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is the first step when making an estimate?","o":["Add the numbers","Round each number","Subtract","Guess"],"a":1,"e":"Always round each number first, then add or subtract the rounded numbers to get your estimate.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 701 rounded to the nearest hundred?","o":["600","700","710","800"],"a":1,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 0, which is less than 5, so round DOWN to 700.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 876 − 324? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["400","500","600","700"],"a":2,"e":"876 rounds to 900, and 324 rounds to 300. Then 900 − 300 = 600.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 545 rounded to the nearest ten?","o":["540","550","500","600"],"a":1,"e":"Look at the ones digit. It is 5, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 550.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 197 + 603? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["700","900","1000","800"],"a":3,"e":"197 rounds to 200, and 603 rounds to 600. Then 200 + 600 = 800.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 382 rounded to the nearest hundred?","o":["300","400","380","390"],"a":1,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 8, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 400.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 33 rounded to the nearest ten?","o":["30","40","33","35"],"a":0,"e":"Look at the ones digit. It is 3, which is less than 5, so round DOWN to 30.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 724 − 283? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["400","500","600","700"],"a":0,"e":"724 rounds to 700, and 283 rounds to 300. Then 700 − 300 = 400.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 850 rounded to the nearest hundred?","o":["800","900","850","860"],"a":1,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 5, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 900.","d":"e"},{"t":"How are estimates different from exact answers?","o":["more than","exactly","less than","close to but not"],"a":3,"e":"Estimates are close to the real answer, but not exactly right. They are a smart guess!","d":"e"},{"t":"45 - 18 = 27. Check: 27 + 18 = ?","o":["45","35","55","43"],"a":0,"e":"To check subtraction, add the answer to the number you subtracted. 27 + 18 = 45. Since this matches the starting number, the subtraction is correct.","d":"e"},{"t":"63 - 29 = 34. Is this correct? Check with addition.","o":["Yes, 34 + 29 = 63","No, 34 + 29 = 53","No, 34 + 29 = 73","Yes, 34 + 29 = 64"],"a":0,"e":"Check: 34 + 29 = 63. Since 63 matches the starting number, the answer 34 is correct.","d":"e"},{"t":"82 - 45 = 37. Check by adding. 37 + 45 = ?","o":["72","82","92","87"],"a":1,"e":"37 + 45 = 82. This matches the starting number, so 82 - 45 = 37 is correct.","d":"m"},{"t":"56 - 23 = 33. Is this correct?","o":["Yes, 33 + 23 = 56","No, the answer should be 43","No, the answer should be 23","Yes, 33 + 23 = 66"],"a":0,"e":"Check: 33 + 23 = 56. This matches, so 56 - 23 = 33 is correct.","d":"e"},{"t":"71 - 38 = 33. Check: 33 + 38 = ?","o":["61","71","81","69"],"a":1,"e":"33 + 38 = 71. This matches the starting number, so 71 - 38 = 33 is correct.","d":"m"},{"t":"How can you check if 94 - 51 = 43 is correct?","o":["Add 43 + 51 and see if it equals 94","Subtract 43 - 51","Add 94 + 51","Subtract 94 - 43 - 51"],"a":0,"e":"To check subtraction, add the answer (43) to the number subtracted (51). If the sum equals the starting number (94), the subtraction is correct. 43 + 51 = 94. Correct!","d":"e"},{"t":"87 - 52 = 35. Check: 35 + 52 = ?","o":["77","87","97","85"],"a":1,"e":"35 + 52 = 87. This matches the starting number, confirming that 87 - 52 = 35 is correct.","d":"m"},{"t":"A student says 76 - 34 = 42. Check with addition. Is the student correct?","o":["Yes, 42 + 34 = 76","No, 42 + 34 = 86","No, 42 + 34 = 66","Yes, 42 + 34 = 78"],"a":0,"e":"Check: 42 + 34 = 76. This matches, so the student is correct: 76 - 34 = 42.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is the best way to check 68 - 25 = 43?","o":["Add: 43 + 25","Subtract again: 68 - 25","Multiply: 43 x 25","Add: 68 + 25"],"a":0,"e":"The best way to check subtraction is to add the answer to the number subtracted: 43 + 25 = 68. Since it matches, the answer is correct.","d":"e"},{"t":"55 - 28 = 27. Check: 27 + 28 = ?","o":["45","55","65","53"],"a":1,"e":"27 + 28 = 55. This matches the starting number, so 55 - 28 = 27 is correct.","d":"m"},{"t":"93 - 47 = 46. Is this correct? Check with addition.","o":["Yes, 46 + 47 = 93","No, 46 + 47 = 83","No, the answer is 56","Yes, 46 + 47 = 94"],"a":0,"e":"Check: 46 + 47 = 93. This matches, so 93 - 47 = 46 is correct.","d":"m"},{"t":"A student wrote 84 - 39 = 55. Check: 55 + 39 = ?","o":["84","94","74","85"],"a":1,"e":"55 + 39 = 94, not 84. Since 94 does not match 84, the student made an error. The correct answer is 84 - 39 = 45.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which addition problem checks 72 - 36 = 36?","o":["36 + 36 = 72","72 + 36 = 108","36 - 36 = 0","72 - 36 = 36"],"a":0,"e":"To check subtraction, add the answer to the number subtracted. 36 + 36 = 72. Since it matches, 72 - 36 = 36 is correct.","d":"m"},{"t":"48 - 19 = 29. Check: 29 + 19 = ?","o":["38","48","58","47"],"a":1,"e":"29 + 19 = 48. This matches the starting number, so 48 - 19 = 29 is correct.","d":"m"},{"t":"A student says 65 - 28 = 47. Is this correct?","o":["No, 47 + 28 = 75, not 65","Yes, 47 + 28 = 65","No, 47 + 28 = 65","Yes, the answer is 47"],"a":0,"e":"Check: 47 + 28 = 75, not 65. The student is wrong. Correct: 65 - 28 = 37. Check: 37 + 28 = 65.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which shows the correct way to check 59 - 23 = 36?","o":["36 + 23 = 59","59 + 23 = 82","36 - 23 = 13","23 + 59 = 82"],"a":0,"e":"Add the answer (36) to the number subtracted (23): 36 + 23 = 59. It matches the starting number, so the subtraction is correct.","d":"m"},{"t":"67 - 41 = 26. Check: 26 + 41 = ?","o":["57","67","77","68"],"a":1,"e":"26 + 41 = 67. This matches, so 67 - 41 = 26 is correct.","d":"m"},{"t":"A boy solved 80 - 35 = 45. He checked: 45 + 35 = 80. Is his work correct?","o":["Yes, his subtraction and check both show 80","No, 45 + 35 = 70","No, 80 - 35 = 55","Yes, but the check is wrong"],"a":0,"e":"45 + 35 = 80, which matches the starting number. Both the subtraction and the check are correct.","d":"m"},{"t":"91 - 56 = 35. Check with addition. 35 + 56 = ?","o":["81","91","101","90"],"a":1,"e":"35 + 56 = 91. This matches the starting number, so 91 - 56 = 35 is correct.","d":"m"},{"t":"A student wrote 74 - 48 = 36. Check: 36 + 48 = ?","o":["74","84","64","76"],"a":1,"e":"36 + 48 = 84, not 74. The student made an error. Correct: 74 - 48 = 26. Check: 26 + 48 = 74.","d":"m"},{"t":"A student wrote: 83 - 47 = 44. Use addition to check. Is this correct?","o":["No, 44 + 47 = 91, not 83. The answer should be 36.","Yes, 44 + 47 = 83","No, the answer should be 46","Yes, 83 - 47 = 44"],"a":0,"e":"Check: 44 + 47 = 91, not 83. The subtraction is wrong. Correct: 83 - 47 = 36. Check: 36 + 47 = 83.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which addition problem correctly checks 125 - 58 = 67?","o":["67 + 58 = 125","125 + 58 = 183","67 + 125 = 192","58 + 58 = 116"],"a":0,"e":"To check subtraction, add the answer to the number you subtracted: 67 + 58 = 125. This matches, so the subtraction is correct.","d":"h"},{"t":"Sam says 92 - 47 = 55. Kim says the answer is 45. Who is right? Use addition to check.","o":["Sam, because 55 + 47 = 102","Kim, because 45 + 47 = 92","Sam, because 55 is bigger","Neither is correct"],"a":1,"e":"Check Sam: 55 + 47 = 102, not 92. Wrong! Check Kim: 45 + 47 = 92. Correct! Kim's answer of 45 is right.","d":"h"},{"t":"__ - 39 = 47. What is the missing number? Use addition to find it.","o":["76","86","96","8"],"a":1,"e":"To find the missing number, add: 47 + 39 = 86. Check: 86 - 39 = 47. The missing number is 86.","d":"h"},{"t":"A student checked their work: 38 + 54 = 92. What subtraction problem were they checking?","o":["92 - 54 = 38","92 - 38 = 64","54 - 38 = 16","92 + 54 = 146"],"a":0,"e":"If the check is 38 + 54 = 92, then the original subtraction was 92 - 54 = 38 (or 92 - 38 = 54). The answer showing is 92 - 54 = 38.","d":"m"},{"t":"True or false: If 67 + 45 = 112, then 112 - 45 = 67.","o":["True, addition and subtraction are inverse operations","False, the numbers are too big","True, but only without regrouping","False, subtraction does not relate to addition"],"a":0,"e":"This is true! Addition and subtraction are inverse (opposite) operations. If adding gives you a sum, then subtracting one addend from the sum gives the other addend.","d":"h"},{"t":"Mia solves 134 - 67 = 67. She checks: 67 + 67 = 134. Is her subtraction correct?","o":["Yes, her check proves it","No, 67 + 67 = 144","No, 134 - 67 = 77","Yes, but the check is wrong"],"a":0,"e":"Check: 67 + 67 = 134. This matches the starting number, so Mia's subtraction 134 - 67 = 67 is correct.","d":"h"},{"t":"A teacher wrote: 95 - 48 = 47. Three students checked differently. Which check is correct?","o":["47 + 48 = 95","95 + 48 = 143","48 - 47 = 1","95 - 47 = 48"],"a":0,"e":"The correct check adds the answer to the subtracted number: 47 + 48 = 95. Option D (95 - 47 = 48) also works as a related fact, but the standard check is addition.","d":"h"},{"t":"David solves 81 - 36 = 55. His check: 55 + 36 = 91. What should David do?","o":["Redo the problem because 91 does not equal 81","Nothing, the answer is correct","Check again because 55 + 36 = 81","Use a different checking method"],"a":0,"e":"55 + 36 = 91, not 81. The check reveals an error. David should redo: 81 - 36 = 45. Check: 45 + 36 = 81.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which pair of number sentences shows related facts?","o":["73 - 28 = 45 and 45 + 28 = 73","73 - 28 = 45 and 73 + 28 = 101","73 - 28 = 45 and 45 - 28 = 17","73 - 28 = 45 and 28 + 45 = 83"],"a":0,"e":"73 - 28 = 45 and 45 + 28 = 73 are related facts (a fact family). They use the same three numbers and show how addition and subtraction are inverses.","d":"e"},{"t":"If you know 56 + 37 = 93, which subtraction fact is also true?","o":["93 - 37 = 56","93 - 37 = 66","56 - 37 = 19","93 + 37 = 130"],"a":0,"e":"Since 56 + 37 = 93, we know 93 - 37 = 56. These are inverse operations using the same three numbers.","d":"m"},{"t":"A student says 'I do not need to check my work if I am careful.' Is this good advice?","o":["No, everyone makes mistakes and checking catches errors","Yes, careful work is always correct","No, but only check hard problems","Yes, checking wastes time"],"a":0,"e":"Even careful students make mistakes! Checking with addition is quick and catches errors before they become problems. Good mathematicians always check their work.","d":"e"},{"t":"__ - 64 = 58. Find the missing number and check your answer.","o":["112","122","132","6"],"a":1,"e":"Add to find the missing number: 58 + 64 = 122. Check: 122 - 64 = 58. The missing number is 122.","d":"h"},{"t":"What are ALL the fact family members for 43 + 29 = 72?","o":["43 + 29 = 72, 29 + 43 = 72, 72 - 29 = 43, 72 - 43 = 29","Only 72 - 29 = 43","43 + 29 = 72 and 72 - 29 = 43 only","There is no fact family"],"a":0,"e":"A fact family has 4 related facts using the same numbers: 43 + 29 = 72, 29 + 43 = 72, 72 - 29 = 43, 72 - 43 = 29.","d":"m"},{"t":"Rosa solved 143 - 85 = 58. She checks: 58 + 85 = 143. Is Rosa correct?","o":["Yes, her check matches so her subtraction is correct","No, 58 + 85 = 133","No, 143 - 85 = 68","Yes, but the check is wrong"],"a":0,"e":"58 + 85 = 143. The check matches the original number, so Rosa's answer is correct.","d":"h"},{"t":"A student solved 110 - 73 = 47. Check this answer.","o":["Wrong: 47 + 73 = 120, not 110","Correct: 47 + 73 = 110","Wrong: 47 + 73 = 110","Correct: the answer is 47"],"a":0,"e":"Check: 47 + 73 = 120, not 110. The answer is wrong. Correct: 110 - 73 = 37. Check: 37 + 73 = 110.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which strategy helps you check 86 - 49?","o":["Find the answer and add it to 49 to see if you get 86","Subtract 49 from 86 twice","Add 86 + 49 = 135","Multiply 86 by 49"],"a":0,"e":"Solve: 86 - 49 = 37. Check by adding the answer to the subtracted number: 37 + 49 = 86. Since it matches, the subtraction is correct.","d":"e"},{"t":"Ben wrote 72 - 38 = 44. His check: 44 + 38 = 82. What does the check tell Ben?","o":["His answer is wrong because 82 does not equal 72","His answer is right because 82 is close to 72","His check is wrong","Nothing useful"],"a":0,"e":"44 + 38 = 82, which does not equal the starting number 72. This tells Ben his answer is wrong. Correct: 72 - 38 = 34. Check: 34 + 38 = 72.","d":"h"},{"t":"If 150 - 83 = 67, which of these is also true?","o":["67 + 83 = 150","150 + 83 = 233","83 - 67 = 16","67 - 83 = 150"],"a":0,"e":"Since 150 - 83 = 67, the inverse is 67 + 83 = 150. These use the same three numbers in a fact family relationship.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ana and Ben both solved 95 - 37. Ana got 58, Ben got 68. Use addition to find who is correct.","o":["Ana, because 58 + 37 = 95","Ben, because 68 + 37 = 95","Both are correct","Neither is correct"],"a":0,"e":"Check Ana: 58 + 37 = 95. Correct! Check Ben: 68 + 37 = 105, not 95. Wrong! Ana's answer of 58 is correct.","d":"h"},{"t":"What number goes in the blank? ___ - 34 = 48. Then check your answer using addition.","o":["72, because 48 + 34 = 82","82, because 48 + 34 = 82 and 82 - 34 = 48","92, because 48 + 34 = 92","78, because 48 + 30 = 78"],"a":1,"e":"Find the missing number by adding: 48 + 34 = 82. Check: 82 - 34 = 48. The answer 82 checks out because the addition confirms it.","d":"h"},{"t":"Carlos solved 153 - 78 = 85. He checked: 85 + 78 = 163. What TWO mistakes did Carlos make?","o":["Wrong subtraction AND wrong addition check","Only wrong subtraction","Only wrong addition","No mistakes were made"],"a":0,"e":"Carlos made two mistakes: (1) 153 - 78 = 75, not 85. (2) His check: 85 + 78 = 163, not 153, which should have told him the answer was wrong. Correct: 75 + 78 = 153.","d":"h"},{"t":"If 67 + 48 = 115, write ALL the subtraction facts in this fact family.","o":["115 - 48 = 67 and 115 - 67 = 48","Only 115 - 48 = 67","115 - 67 = 48 only","67 - 48 = 19 and 48 - 67 = impossible"],"a":0,"e":"A fact family uses the same three numbers. From 67 + 48 = 115: the two subtraction facts are 115 - 48 = 67 and 115 - 67 = 48.","d":"h"},{"t":"A student solved 140 - 65 = 85. She checked: 85 + 65 = 150. She says 'It is close enough, so I am right.' Is she correct?","o":["No, the check must match exactly, and 150 does not equal 140","Yes, close enough is fine in math","No, but only because the difference is more than 5","Yes, 150 and 140 are close"],"a":0,"e":"In math, 'close enough' is not correct. 85 + 65 = 150, not 140, so the subtraction has an error. Correct: 140 - 65 = 75. Check: 75 + 65 = 140 exactly.","d":"h"},{"t":"Nora solved three problems. Which one has an error? A) 91 - 45 = 46  B) 83 - 37 = 46  C) 72 - 28 = 54","o":["Problem C, because 54 + 28 = 82, not 72","Problem A, because 46 + 45 = 91","Problem B, because 46 + 37 = 83","None have errors"],"a":0,"e":"Check each: A) 46 + 45 = 91. Correct! B) 46 + 37 = 83. Correct! C) 54 + 28 = 82, not 72. Error! The correct answer for C is 72 - 28 = 44.","d":"h"},{"t":"A number minus 56 gives 47. Use the checking strategy to also find: that same number minus 47.","o":["56","47","103","9"],"a":0,"e":"Find the number: 47 + 56 = 103. Now: 103 - 47 = 56. The fact family connects both: if 103 - 56 = 47, then 103 - 47 = 56.","d":"h"},{"t":"Tom checked 86 - 39 by computing 39 + 86 = 125. What is wrong with Tom's checking strategy?","o":["He should add the ANSWER to 39, not 86 to 39","Nothing, his strategy is fine","He should subtract instead of add","He should multiply to check"],"a":0,"e":"Tom added the wrong numbers. To check, he needs to add the ANSWER (86 - 39 = 47) to the number subtracted (39): 47 + 39 = 86. Tom mistakenly added 39 + 86.","d":"h"},{"t":"Three students solved 132 - 67. Amy: 65. Ben: 75. Cal: 55. Which student is correct?","o":["Amy, because 65 + 67 = 132","Ben, because 75 + 67 = 132","Cal, because 55 + 67 = 132","None of them"],"a":0,"e":"Check each: Amy: 65 + 67 = 132. Correct! Ben: 75 + 67 = 142. Wrong! Cal: 55 + 67 = 122. Wrong! Amy is correct.","d":"h"},{"t":"Why does adding the answer to the subtracted number prove the subtraction is correct?","o":["Because addition undoes subtraction -- they are inverse operations","Because adding always gives bigger numbers","Because the teacher said so","It does not actually prove it"],"a":0,"e":"Addition and subtraction are inverse operations -- they undo each other. If A - B = C, then C + B must equal A. This inverse relationship is what makes the check work.","d":"e"},{"t":"Lisa solved 148 - 79 = 69. She also solved 148 - 69 = 79. Both check out as a fact family. Is she right?","o":["Yes, 69 + 79 = 148 confirms both are correct","No, 69 + 79 = 138, not 148","Yes, but only the first equation","No, you cannot have two related facts"],"a":0,"e":"Check: 69 + 79 = 148. This confirms both: 148 - 79 = 69 and 148 - 69 = 79. These are both part of the same fact family.","d":"h"},{"t":"A student solved 95 - 38 = 57 and then 95 - 57 = 48. She says both are right. What error do you see?","o":["The second equation is wrong: 95 - 57 = 38, not 48","Both equations are wrong","The first equation is wrong","No errors"],"a":0,"e":"The first is correct: 57 + 38 = 95. But the second is wrong: 95 - 57 should equal 38 (from the fact family), not 48. The student made a subtraction error on the second problem.","d":"h"},{"t":"Jake knows 156 - 89 = 67. Without solving, what is 156 - 67?","o":["89, because it is the other subtraction in the fact family","99","79","Cannot tell without solving"],"a":0,"e":"Since 156 - 89 = 67, the fact family tells us 156 - 67 = 89. No new calculation needed! The three numbers (156, 89, 67) always work together.","d":"h"},{"t":"A student checked 113 - 47 = 66 by computing 66 + 47. She got 113. But the real answer is 113 - 47 = 66. How is this possible?","o":["The answer IS 66 and the check proves it","The check must be wrong","66 + 47 cannot equal 113","She got lucky"],"a":0,"e":"113 - 47 = 66 is correct. The check confirms it: 66 + 47 = 113. When the check sum matches the original number, the subtraction is proven correct.","d":"h"},{"t":"Emma solved 167 - 89 = 78. She wants to check but finds addition hard too. What easier check can she use?","o":["Estimate: 170 - 90 = 80, and 78 is close to 80, so it is likely correct","There is no other way to check","Multiply 78 by 89","Subtract 78 from 89"],"a":0,"e":"Estimation is a great quick check! 170 - 90 = 80, and 78 is close to 80, supporting the answer. For certainty, do the addition check: 78 + 89 = 167. Correct!","d":"h"},{"t":"Two problems use the same three numbers. If 94 - 56 = 38, what MUST be true?","o":["38 + 56 = 94 and 94 - 38 = 56","56 - 38 = 94","94 + 56 = 38","Only 38 + 56 = 94 is true"],"a":0,"e":"From 94 - 56 = 38, the fact family gives us: 38 + 56 = 94, 56 + 38 = 94, and 94 - 38 = 56. All three numbers stay connected through inverse operations.","d":"m"},{"t":"A class solved 125 - 67. Five students got 58 and three got 68. Use checking to settle the debate.","o":["58 is correct: 58 + 67 = 125","68 is correct: 68 + 67 = 125","Both could be correct","Neither is correct"],"a":0,"e":"Check 58: 58 + 67 = 125. Correct! Check 68: 68 + 67 = 135, not 125. Wrong! The answer is 58. The three students who got 68 likely forgot to regroup properly.","d":"h"},{"t":"Dan solved a subtraction problem and got 49. He added 49 + 36 and got 85. What was the original problem?","o":["85 - 36 = 49","49 - 36 = 13","85 + 36 = 121","36 - 49 = impossible"],"a":0,"e":"If Dan's check is 49 + 36 = 85, then the original subtraction was 85 - 36 = 49. The addition check reveals the original problem's structure.","d":"h"},{"t":"Mia made the same error on two problems: 82 - 35 = 53 and 71 - 24 = 53. What pattern of error is she making?","o":["She is not regrouping -- she subtracts the smaller digit from the larger in ones place","She is adding instead of subtracting","She is guessing","Her answers are correct"],"a":0,"e":"82 - 35: Mia did 5 - 2 = 3 (wrong direction), 8 - 3 = 5, getting 53. Correct: 47. 71 - 24: Mia did 4 - 1 = 3, 7 - 2 = 5, getting 53. Correct: 47. She consistently subtracts the smaller ones digit from the larger instead of regrouping.","d":"h"},{"t":"If 89 + 43 = 132, write the complete fact family. How many facts are in it?","o":["4 facts: 89+43=132, 43+89=132, 132-43=89, 132-89=43","2 facts","3 facts","6 facts"],"a":0,"e":"The complete fact family has 4 facts: 89 + 43 = 132, 43 + 89 = 132, 132 - 43 = 89, 132 - 89 = 43. All use the same three numbers.","d":"h"},{"t":"A student says 'If my subtraction check does not match, I should just erase and write the addition answer instead.' Is this good advice?","o":["No, she should redo the subtraction carefully to find the error","Yes, the addition answer is always right","No, she should try a third method","Yes, because addition is easier"],"a":0,"e":"If the check does not match, she should redo the subtraction step by step. The check only tells you there is an error -- it does not automatically give the right answer. She needs to find WHERE the mistake happened.","d":"e"}],"quiz":[{"t":"What is 274 rounded to the nearest hundred?","o":["300","200","270","280"],"a":0,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 7, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 300."},{"t":"What is 435 rounded to the nearest ten?","o":["430","400","440","500"],"a":2,"e":"Look at the ones digit. It is 5, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 440."},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 312 + 489? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["800","700","900","600"],"a":0,"e":"312 rounds to 300, and 489 rounds to 500. Then 300 + 500 = 800."},{"t":"What is 765 rounded to the nearest hundred?","o":["700","760","800","770"],"a":2,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 6, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 800."},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 638 − 192? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["300","500","400","600"],"a":2,"e":"638 rounds to 600, and 192 rounds to 200. Then 600 − 200 = 400."},{"t":"What is the first step to estimate 347 + 256?","o":["Add them","Round each number","Subtract instead","Multiply by 10"],"a":1,"e":"Always round each number first, then add or subtract the rounded numbers to get your estimate."}]}],"unitQuiz":[{"t":"What is 347 + 286?","o":["572","681","633","714"],"a":2,"e":"Add the ones first: 7 + 6 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 4 + 8 + 1 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 3 + 2 + 1 = 6. The answer is 633.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 456 + 378?","o":["834","762","871","913"],"a":0,"e":"Add the ones first: 6 + 8 = 14, write 4 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 5 + 7 + 1 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 4 + 3 + 1 = 8. The answer is 834.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 742 − 385?","o":["284","413","526","357"],"a":3,"e":"You need to regroup twice! Work from right to left, regrouping when the top digit is smaller. The answer is 357.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 600 − 245?","o":["283","355","412","521"],"a":1,"e":"The ones and tens are both 0, so regroup from the hundreds first. The answer is 355.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 523 + 349?","o":["872","801","913","754"],"a":0,"e":"Add the ones first: 3 + 9 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 2 + 4 + 1 = 7. Then hundreds: 5 + 3 = 8. The answer is 872.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 800 − 367?","o":["364","512","276","433"],"a":3,"e":"Both the tens and ones are 0, so regroup from the hundreds and work through each column. The answer is 433.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is 274 rounded to the nearest 100?","o":["200","270","300","280"],"a":2,"e":"Look at the tens digit. It is 7, which is 5 or more, so round UP to 300.","d":"h"},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 489 + 312? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["700","800","900","600"],"a":1,"e":"489 rounds to 500, and 312 rounds to 300. Then 500 + 300 = 800.","d":"h"},{"t":"What is 267 + 435?","o":["702","651","743","815"],"a":0,"e":"Add the ones first: 7 + 5 = 12, write 2 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 6 + 3 + 1 = 10, write 0 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 2 + 4 + 1 = 7. The answer is 702.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 900 − 536?","o":["291","423","512","364"],"a":3,"e":"Both the ones and tens are 0, so regroup from the hundreds first and work through each column. The answer is 364.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is the best estimate for 197 + 312? (Round to the nearest hundred first.)","o":["400","600","500","700"],"a":2,"e":"197 rounds to 200, and 312 rounds to 300. Then 200 + 300 = 500.","d":"h"},{"t":"What is 451 + 279?","o":["653","730","781","912"],"a":1,"e":"Add the ones first: 1 + 9 = 10, write 0 and regroup 1 ten. Then tens: 5 + 7 + 1 = 13, write 3 and regroup 1 ten. Then hundreds: 4 + 2 + 1 = 7. The answer is 730.","d":"e"},{"t":"What is 705 − 348?","o":["284","423","516","357"],"a":3,"e":"Ones: 5 is less than 8, so regroup to get 15 − 8 = 7. Tens: after regrouping from hundreds, 9 − 4 = 5. Hundreds: 6 − 3 = 3. The answer is 357.","